  "text": "The error string 'mvcc: required revision has been compacted' originates from the upstream etcd repository at etcd-io/etcd, not from the Kubernetes vendored copies. The authoritative source consists of two files: (1) server/mvcc/kvstore.go, where the ErrCompacted error variable is defined at line 39 as `errors.New(\"mvcc: required revision has been compacted\")`; and (2) server/mvcc/kvstore_txn.go, where the rangeKeys method (defined at line 128 on the storeTxnRead type) returns this error at line 137 when `rev < tr.s.compactMainRev`, indicating that the requested revision has been compacted and is no longer available. This is the core MVCC (Multi-Version Concurrency Control) logic in etcd that performs compaction and detects when clients request revisions that have been garbage-collected. While Kubernetes/kubernetes contains vendored copies of etcd code under vendor/go.etcd.io/etcd/ (which are identical but stale copies of the source), and the Kubernetes apiserver also has an error-mapping layer at staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/etcd3/errors.go that translates this error into Kubernetes error types, neither of these are the authoritative source. The error originates and should be tracked in the upstream etcd-io/etcd repository."
}

